      "writtenOn": "2026-05-14T11:26:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good catch — pursued this and rewrote the fix to be much simpler. The bug only manifests when a TryClause.yield\u0027s save/reset/restore of `c.skipTry` brackets the evaluation of a sibling failing ?-reference (the restore erases the signal). When the inner try body lexically contains no ?-marked references, it cannot itself fail, so the save/restore is pure overhead — and the only thing that can erase outer signals.\n\nNew approach: track `BodyHasOptional bool` on TryClause at compile time (via a counter snapshot on the compiler), and gate the save/reset/restore on it. The per-reference TryClause pointer, runtime tryStack, OrphanTryClause sentinel, and compile-time TryClause stack are all gone. Net diff vs the pre-fix state is +33/-4 across 2 files (was +87/-47 across 7).\n\nPTAL.",
      "parentUuid": "6a5c86d4_0e1e6d64",
      "revId": "85ebaf7d0b889559ebbfcb8f867682d104390082",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
